NAME:
   rpt - repeat running a command a number of times

USAGE:
   rpt [OPTIONS] COMMAND [ARGUMENTS...]

VERSION:
   dev

DESCRIPTION:
   Repeatedly run COMMAND with ARGUMENTS.  The number of times to run COMMAND
   is determined by OPTIONS.

AUTHOR:
   Ben Armston

OPTIONS:
   --times TIMES, -t TIMES        number of TIMES to run COMMAND (default: 1)
   --delay DURATION, -d DURATION  wait DURATION between runs (default: 0s)
   --verbose, -v                  print debugging messages (default: false)
   --help, -h                     show help
   --version                      print the version

